text: Colonel Axel Walfrid Carl Gyllenkrok (9 August 1888 - 8 August 1946) was a Swedish officer and sports shooter. He competed in two events at the 1912 Summer Olympics. ==Dates of rank== *1908 – Underlöjtnant *1911 – Lieutenant *1920 – Captain (Army) *1928 – Captain (Air Force) *1929 – Major (Army) *1932 – Major (Air Force) *1936 – Lieutenant Colonel *1937 – Colonel ==References== ==External links== *Article at Svenskt biografiskt lexikon Category:1888 births Category:1946 deaths Category:Swedish Army colonels Category:Swedish Air Force officers Category:Swedish male sport shooters Category:Olympic shooters of Sweden Category:Shooters at the 1912 Summer Olympics Category:People from Karlskrona Category:Members of the Royal Swedish Academy of War Sciences
